          <article class="work-item">
            <p class="work-tag">Journal platform</p>
            <h2>World Scholars Journal Series</h2>
            <p>
              Concept for a shared platform for several journals, each with its own call for papers,
              editorial board, and issue archive under a consistent layout.
            </p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
              <li>Shard template across multiple journals</li>
              <li>Simple access to current calls and archives</li>
              <li>Clean author and reviewer information</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <article class="work-item">
            <p class="work-tag">Academic portfolio</p>
            <h2>Computational Sociology Lab</h2>
            <p>
              Personal academic home concept for combining quantitative, qualitative, and policy work.
              Sections for research, teaching, and public outputs in one coherent structure.
            </p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
              <li>Landing page with clear summary</li>
              <li>Project list with short descriptions</li>
              <li>Links to code repositories and data</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <article class="work-item">
            <p class="work-tag">Teaching project</p>
            <h2>Methods teaching site</h2>
            <p>
              A compact site for a research methods course with weekly topics, readings,
              and assignment descriptions for students.
            </p>
            <ul class="bullet-list">
              <li>Week by week structure</li>
              <li>Download sections for syllabi and slides</li>
              <li>Optional simple FAQ for students</li>
